column5: serving a K-6 population. The school is located in southeast\rof San Diego County in the city of Chula Vista. It is located in an area of new homes and apartments.\rVeterans is about five miles from the U.S./Mexico border. Veterans was the 43rd elementary school\rto open in the Chula Vista Elementary School District. The school has four permanent classroom\rpods
column8: and an administrative building.\r\r--------\rWe have a very diverse student population. Approximately 23% of the students qualify for the free\rChula Vista Elementary School\rand reduced National School Lunch Program. Approximately 20% of the students are English\rDistrict\rLearners

column20: supportive learning environment for every\rArmando Fariasmember of the school community. We foster the continuous academic and social growth of all\r\rstudents by engaging them in challenging
